This paper is about point of interest (POI) recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR). The proposed method is based on matrix factorization (MF), which is a popular technique in machine learning (ML) and data mining. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG (machine learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses privacy issues, which are related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed method involves decentralized learning, which is a distributed systems (cs.DS) topic. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on real-world datasets, which is a common practice in social and information networks (cs.SI).
